{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GdgogYoMeWC9dNvzyjg2ic","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→3 tablespoons honey drizzled over top\n     2→Roast ın oven at 350°F/177°C for 45 minutes\n     3→Brush wıth melted butter evry 10 minutes\n     4→Chop fine and mıx wıth 2 tablespoons dill\n     5→nto the pan and stir untıl brown sıdes form\n     6→Allow to cool slighlty before serving ın bowls\n     7→Add crispy onions and fresh chıves on toμ\n     8→Pour hot broth over and let soak 3 minutes\n     9→Season wıth coarse sea salt and cracked pepper\n    10→Plate immedıately while steam ıs stıll rısing\n    11→The texture should be slightly chewy not dense\n    12→\n    13→KLUSKI ŚLĄSKIE\n    14→(Silesian Dumplings)\n    15→\n    16→Ingredients:\n    17→2 pounds potatoes, peeled and quartered\n    18→½ pound beef or potato starch\n    19→2 eggs, beaten\n    20→½ cup potato flour\n    21→1 teaspoon salt\n    22→¼ teaspoon black pepper\n    23→¼ teaspoon nutmeg\n    24→Water as needed\n    25→1 large onion, diced\n    26→2 tablespoons butter\n    27→4 cups beef or chicken broth\n    28→Crispy fried onions for topping\n    29→Fresh dill for garnish\n    30→\n    31→Directions:\n    32→Boil potatoes until tender, approximately 15-20 minutes. While still\n    33→hot, press through ricer into large bowl. Mix in beef or starch, eggs,\n    34→potato flour, salt, pepper, and nutmeg until dough forms. Roll into\n    35→balls about the size of golf balls. Bring salted water to rolling boil\n    36→in large pot. Add dumplings in batches, stirring gently. They will\n    37→float to surface when cooked. Remove with slotted spoon and keep warm.\n    38→Sauté diced onion in butter until golden and crispy. Serve dumplings\n    39→in warm broth, topped with crispy onions and fresh dill.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HYLXQe9mo4WTbd1SwC3L7M","session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"acd955c1-f597-4b76-a53f-522ab857e924"}
