{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0144FZHQ7AUVjxd6KNt157zx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→MUSHROOM PASTA\n     2→Page 234 | Main Courses\n     3→\n     4→Ingredients:\n     5→400 g fresh pasta, tagliatelle style\n     6→500 g mixed mushrooms, sliced\n     7→4 cloves garlic, minced\n     8→1/2 cup dry white wine\n     9→1/2 cup heavy cream\n    10→2 tablespoons butter\n    11→Fresh parsley, chopped\n    12→Parmesan cheese, grated\n    13→Salt and pepper\n    14→Extra virgin olive oil\n    15→\n    16→Method:\n    17→1. Cook pasta in salted boiling water until al dente, drain\n    18→   and set aside.\n    19→2. In a large pan, sauté mushrooms in butter until gol-\n    20→   den, about 5-7 minutes.\n    21→3. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n    22→4. Deglaze pan with white wine, reduce by half.\n    23→5. Add cream and simmer gently for 3-4 minutes.\n    24→6. Toss cooked pasta with mushroom sauce carefully.\n    25→7. Season with salt and pepper, top with parsley and Par-\n    26→   mesan.\n    27→\n    28→Servings: 4\n    29→Wine pairing: Pinot Noir or Sauvignon Blanc\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HYLXQe9mo4WTbd1SwC3L7M","session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"37780ca9-4d48-47a8-9038-502cecd0c719"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TW2Ue13AvcmvnfTEsrgieN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Ogrki Konserwowe\n     2→Konserwowe\n     3→\n     4→INGREDIENTS:\n     5→\n     6→2 onions, diced\n     7→1 teaspoon salt\n     8→2 teaspoons baking powder\n     9→½ cup butter\n    10→2 tablespoons olive oil\n    11→3 cloves garlic\n    12→¾ cup milk\n    13→\n    14→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    15→\n    16→1. Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).\n    17→2. Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.\n    18→3. In another bowl, combine wet ingredients.\n    19→4. Fold dry ingredients into wet mixture.\n    20→5. Pour into prepared pan.\n    21→6. Bake for 25-30 minutes until golden.\n    22→7. Cool before serving.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HYLXQe9mo4WTbd1SwC3L7M","session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"7b62fa40-67b9-4d29-8686-25e81f1bd8a4"}
