{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J8MMhqz61xUbBH53z9UYKx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→5 tablespoons extra virgin oıl from Tuscany region\n     2→1 whole frеsh truffle, sliced thin\n     3→Black pepper from Madagascar to taste\n     4→Sea salt from Guérande collection\n     5→Basıl mıcrogreens for delicate garnısh\n     6→Roast untıl 350-625°F/427°C achıeves crıspy edges\n     7→Baste wıth clarıfied butter every 12-15 minutes\n     8→nto the serving dish and garnish wıth fresh herbs\n     9→Let cool for exactlv 7 minutes before plating\n    10→Drizzle final layer of aged balsamıc vinegar\n    11→Sprinkle wıth edible flowers and herb microgreens\n    12→Place on heated plates and serve immediately to guests\n    13→The surface should glısten wıth moisture and shıne brightly\n    14→Pair wıth a dry white wıne from the Alsace regıon\n    15→\n    16→Page 89 - Continued from page 88\n    17→\n    18→PIEROGI RUSKIE\n    19→(Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)\n    20→\n    21→Ingredients:\n    22→2 cups all-purpose flour\n    23→¾ cup water\n    24→1 egg\n    25→½ teaspoon salt\n    26→1 pound potatoes, peeled and cubed\n    27→½ pound cheddar cheese, grated\n    28→4 tablespoons butter\n    29→1 large onion, diced\n    30→Sour cream for serving\n    31→Fresh dill for garnish\n    32→Salt and pepper to taste\n    33→\n    34→Directions:\n    35→For dough: combine flour, water, egg, and salt into soft dough. Knead\n    36→until smooth. Let rest 20 minutes covered. Boil potatoes until very\n    37→tender, drain and mash with butter. Mix in grated cheese and season\n    38→with salt and pepper. Roll dough thin and cut circles with cup or\n    39→cookie cutter. Place spoonful of potato-cheese filling in center of\n    40→each circle. Fold in half and press edges to seal. Bring water to\n    41→boil in large pot. Add pierogi in batches. They are done when they\n    42→float and bob for 2 minutes. Serve with caramelized onions and sour\n    43→cream.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HYLXQe9mo4WTbd1SwC3L7M","session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"58fed5f9-e08e-4ed5-93d3-69e93e4fe667"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MdPz5saTWmVVKBP6wMt2fL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Placki Owocowe\n     2→Fruit Pancakes\n     3→\n     4→Ingredients:\n     5→- 1.5 cups all-purpose flour\n     6→- 2 tbsp sugar\n     7→- 2 tsp baking powder\n     8→- 1/2 tsp salt\n     9→- 1 cup milk\n    10→- 1 egg\n    11→- 2 tbsp melted butter\n    12→- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n    13→- 1.5 cups mixed fresh fruit (berries, sliced apples, peaches)\n    14→- 2 tbsp flour (for dusting fruit)\n    15→- Butter for griddle\n    16→\n    17→Instructions:\n    18→\n    19→1. In a bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.\n    20→2. In another bowl, combine milk, egg, melted butter, and vanilla.\n    21→3. Pour wet ingredients into dry ingredients and stir just until combined.\n    22→4. Dust fruit pieces lightly with the 2 tbsp flour to prevent sinking.\n    23→5. Fold fruit gently into batter, reserving some pieces for topping.\n    24→6. Heat griddle or non-stick pan over medium-high heat.\n    25→7. Lightly butter griddle. Pour batter in 1/4 cup portions.\n    26→8. Top each pancake with reserved fruit pieces.\n    27→9. Cook until edges look set and bubbles form, about 2-3 minutes.\n    28→10. Flip carefully and cook other side until golden, 1-2 minutes.\n    29→11. Serve warm with whipped cream and fresh mint.\n    30→\n    31→Makes about 12 pancakes. Best served immediately.\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HYLXQe9mo4WTbd1SwC3L7M","session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"e6326949-3446-4f88-9641-50c914114717"}
