{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016C6tAkG3vmzq5CrWN7pTBY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Polenta with Wild Mushrooms\n     2→\n     3→Creamy polenta is an Italian comfort food that deserves a place in every home cook's rotation. When topped with\n     4→sautéed wild mushrooms in a rich garlic and herb sauce, it becomes an elegant dish worthy of special occasions.\n     5→This recipe works wonderfully as a vegetarian main course or as a sophisticated side dish alongside roasted meats.\n     6→The beauty of polenta lies in its versatility and the fact that it can be prepared several hours ahead. The mushroom\n     7→ragù improves with time, developing deeper flavors as it sits. This is the kind of dish that warms both body and soul\n     8→on cool autumn and winter evenings.\n     9→\n    10→Ingredients (serves 4)\n    11→\n    12→For the Polenta:\n    13→4 cups vegetable broth\n    14→1 cup whole milk\n    15→1 cup polenta (cornmeal)\n    16→4 tbsp butter\n    17→2 oz Parmesan cheese, grated\n    18→Salt and white pepper\n    19→\n    20→For the Mushrooms:\n    21→1.5 lbs mixed wild mushrooms (cremini, shiitake, oyster), sliced\n    22→4 cloves garlic, minced\n    23→2 shallots, minced\n    24→1 cup dry white wine\n    25→1 cup vegetable or chicken broth\n    26→1/2 cup heavy cream\n    27→3 tbsp olive oil\n    28→2 tbsp fresh thyme leaves\n    29→2 bay leaves\n    30→Salt and pepper to taste\n    31→Fresh parsley for garnish\n    32→\n    33→Instructions\n    34→\n    35→1. For polenta: Bring broth and milk to boil in large pot\n    36→2. Whisk polenta slowly into liquid to avoid lumps\n    37→3. Reduce heat to low and stir constantly for 30-40 minutes\n    38→4. Polenta should pull away from sides of pot\n    39→5. Stir in butter and Parmesan, season with salt and pepper\n    40→6. For mushrooms: Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat\n    41→7. Add mushrooms in batches, cooking until golden and moisture evaporates\n    42→8. Add garlic and shallots, cook 2 minutes more\n    43→9. Deglaze pan with white wine, scraping up browned bits\n    44→10. Add broth, thyme, and bay leaves\n    45→11. Simmer 20 minutes until flavors meld\n    46→12. Stir in cream and season with salt and pepper\n    47→13. Spoon polenta onto plates and top with mushroom ragù\n    48→14. Garnish with fresh parsley\n    49→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HYLXQe9mo4WTbd1SwC3L7M","session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"f9674c6a-def3-45a6-8fdd-e2dbd187b528"}
