{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QKfDgfNKP4DuzVkZLuVyQt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Dania główne | Jesień | PRZYGOTOWANIE 20 MIN | GOTOWANIE 2 H 30 MIN\n     2→\n     3→BEEF STEW\n     4→\n     5→Ingredients:\n     6→2 lbs beef chuck, cubed\n     7→3 tablespoons olive oil\n     8→1 large onion, diced\n     9→4 cloves garlic, minced\n    10→3 carrots, chunked\n    11→3 potatoes, cubed\n    12→2 cups beef broth\n    13→1 cup red wine\n    14→2 bay leaves\n    15→1 teaspoon dried thyme\n    16→Salt and pepper to taste\n    17→2 tablespoons tomato paste\n    18→\n    19→Instructions:\n    20→1. Heat oil in a heavy pot over medium-high heat\n    21→2. Brown beef in batches, set aside\n    22→3. Sauté onion and garlic until fragrant\n    23→4. Add tomato paste and cook 1 minute\n    24→5. Return beef to pot\n    25→6. Add broth, wine, and herbs\n    26→7. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour 45 minutes\n    27→8. Add carrots and potatoes\n    28→9. Continue simmering another 45 minutes until vegetables are tender\n    29→10. Season with salt and pepper\n    30→11. Serve hot in bowls with crusty bread\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"c7e02985-10d9-42a0-b2c7-cf874514507a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beef Stew.generated.18.txt","content":"Dania główne | Jesień | PRZYGOTOWANIE 20 MIN | GOTOWANIE 2 H 30 MIN\n\nBEEF STEW\n\nIngredients:\n2 lbs beef chuck, cubed\n3 tablespoons olive oil\n1 large onion, diced\n4 cloves garlic, minced\n3 carrots, chunked\n3 potatoes, cubed\n2 cups beef broth\n1 cup red wine\n2 bay leaves\n1 teaspoon dried thyme\nSalt and pepper to taste\n2 tablespoons tomato paste\n\nInstructions:\n1. Heat oil in a heavy pot over medium-high heat\n2. Brown beef in batches, set aside\n3. Sauté onion and garlic until fragrant\n4. Add tomato paste and cook 1 minute\n5. Return beef to pot\n6. Add broth, wine, and herbs\n7. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour 45 minutes\n8. Add carrots and potatoes\n9. Continue simmering another 45 minutes until vegetables are tender\n10. Season with salt and pepper\n11. Serve hot in bowls with crusty bread\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
