{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SguZ6iJom1Qbfd6u82NJ4e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→CHOCOLATE BROWNIES + FUDGY CHOCOLATE BROWNIES\n     2→\n     3→CLASSIC CHOCOLATE BROWNIES\n     4→\n     5→Ingredients:\n     6→- 115g butter\n     7→- 200g dark chocolate, chopped\n     8→- 200g sugar\n     9→- 2 large eggs\n    10→- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n    11→- 90g all-purpose flour\n    12→- 25g cocoa powder\n    13→- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n    14→- 100g chocolate chips (optional)\n    15→\n    16→Instructions:\n    17→1. Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F).\n    18→2. Melt butter and chocolate together in double boiler.\n    19→3. Whisk sugar with eggs until pale, then add vanilla.\n    20→4. Combine chocolate mixture with egg mixture.\n    21→5. Fold in flour, cocoa powder, and salt until just combined.\n    22→6. Fold in chocolate chips if using.\n    23→7. Pour into greased 8x8 inch pan.\n    24→8. Bake 25-30 minutes until set but fudgy in center.\n    25→9. Cool in pan 30 minutes before cutting into squares.\n    26→Yields 16 brownies.\n    27→\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→FUDGY CHOCOLATE BROWNIES (Ultra-Decadent Variation)\n    31→\n    32→Add to the above recipe:\n    33→- Extra 50g dark chocolate, chopped\n    34→- 1 tablespoon additional butter\n    35→- Reduce flour to 70g (creates denser, fudgier texture)\n    36→- 2 tablespoons espresso powder mixed with 1 tablespoon hot water\n    37→\n    38→Instructions modified:\n    39→Follow classic recipe but increase chocolate quantities and reduce flour.\n    40→Stir espresso mixture into melted chocolate for depth.\n    41→Reduce baking time to 20-25 minutes for extra fudgy center.\n    42→Insert toothpick—it should come out slightly wet.\n    43→\n    44→Both versions freeze beautifully for up to 3 months.\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"55000049-bd11-4d59-a1b1-3cabcd9f1436","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Chocolate Brownies + Fudgy Chocolate Brownies.generated.18.txt","content":"CHOCOLATE BROWNIES + FUDGY CHOCOLATE BROWNIES\n\nCLASSIC CHOCOLATE BROWNIES\n\nIngredients:\n- 115g butter\n- 200g dark chocolate, chopped\n- 200g sugar\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 90g all-purpose flour\n- 25g cocoa powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 100g chocolate chips (optional)\n\nInstructions:\n1. Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F).\n2. Melt butter and chocolate together in double boiler.\n3. Whisk sugar with eggs until pale, then add vanilla.\n4. Combine chocolate mixture with egg mixture.\n5. Fold in flour, cocoa powder, and salt until just combined.\n6. Fold in chocolate chips if using.\n7. Pour into greased 8x8 inch pan.\n8. Bake 25-30 minutes until set but fudgy in center.\n9. Cool in pan 30 minutes before cutting into squares.\nYields 16 brownies.\n\n---\n\nFUDGY CHOCOLATE BROWNIES (Ultra-Decadent Variation)\n\nAdd to the above recipe:\n- Extra 50g dark chocolate, chopped\n- 1 tablespoon additional butter\n- Reduce flour to 70g (creates denser, fudgier texture)\n- 2 tablespoons espresso powder mixed with 1 tablespoon hot water\n\nInstructions modified:\nFollow classic recipe but increase chocolate quantities and reduce flour.\nStir espresso mixture into melted chocolate for depth.\nReduce baking time to 20-25 minutes for extra fudgy center.\nInsert toothpick—it should come out slightly wet.\n\nBoth versions freeze beautifully for up to 3 months.\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}}}
