{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NdNM7Cu3rEC82T2KJzPiWu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION\n     2→\n     3→HERB BAKED SALMON\n     4→\n     5→Ingredients:\n     6→- 4 salmon fillets (6 oz each)\n     7→- 3 tbsp olive oil\n     8→- 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice\n     9→- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n    10→- 1 tsp dried oregano\n    11→- 1 tsp dried thyme\n    12→- 1/2 tsp dried rosemary\n    13→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    14→- Lemon slices for garnish\n    15→- Fresh parsley\n    16→\n    17→Instructions:\n    18→\n    19→1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n    20→2. Place salmon fillets on parchment-lined baking sheet.\n    21→3. Mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, and rosemary.\n    22→4. Brush herb mixture over salmon fillets.\n    23→5. Season with salt and pepper.\n    24→6. Arrange lemon slices on top.\n    25→7. Bake for 12-15 minutes until fish flakes easily.\n    26→8. Serve immediately garnished with parsley.\n    27→\n    28→Serves 4.\n    29→\n    30→---\n    31→\n    32→DILL SAUCE VARIATION\n    33→\n    34→Ingredients:\n    35→- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n    36→- 3 tbsp fresh dill, finely chopped\n    37→- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n    38→- 1 clove garlic, minced\n    39→- 1/2 tsp Dijon mustard\n    40→- Salt and white pepper\n    41→- Cucumber slices (optional)\n    42→\n    43→Instructions:\n    44→\n    45→1. Combine Greek yogurt with fresh dill in bowl.\n    46→2. Add lemon juice, minced garlic, and mustard.\n    47→3. Whisk until smooth and well combined.\n    48→4. Season with salt and white pepper to taste.\n    49→5. Fold in diced cucumber if using.\n    50→6. Serve as accompaniment to herb baked salmon.\n    51→7. Can be made 4 hours ahead.\n    52→\n    53→Makes approximately 1 cup sauce.\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"dbf75f6c-a366-4f46-b822-3149e65b6860","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION.generated.18.txt","content":"HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION\n\nHERB BAKED SALMON\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 salmon fillets (6 oz each)\n- 3 tbsp olive oil\n- 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp dried thyme\n- 1/2 tsp dried rosemary\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Lemon slices for garnish\n- Fresh parsley\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).\n2. Place salmon fillets on parchment-lined baking sheet.\n3. Mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, and rosemary.\n4. Brush herb mixture over salmon fillets.\n5. Season with salt and pepper.\n6. Arrange lemon slices on top.\n7. Bake for 12-15 minutes until fish flakes easily.\n8. Serve immediately garnished with parsley.\n\nServes 4.\n\n---\n\nDILL SAUCE VARIATION\n\nIngredients:\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 3 tbsp fresh dill, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- 1/2 tsp Dijon mustard\n- Salt and white pepper\n- Cucumber slices (optional)\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Combine Greek yogurt with fresh dill in bowl.\n2. Add lemon juice, minced garlic, and mustard.\n3. Whisk until smooth and well combined.\n4. Season with salt and white pepper to taste.\n5. Fold in diced cucumber if using.\n6. Serve as accompaniment to herb baked salmon.\n7. Can be made 4 hours ahead.\n\nMakes approximately 1 cup sauce.\n","numLines":54,"startLine":1,"totalLines":54}}}
