{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S5ToRdD8DvNfEY5kYbXAwF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PAELLA\n     2→VALENCIANA\n     3→\n     4→Traditional Spanish rice dish from Valencia region\n     5→\n     6→Ingredients:\n     7→- 400g short-grain rice (bomba or arborio)\n     8→- 1 liter chicken or vegetable broth\n     9→- 150g green beans\n    10→- 100g butter beans\n    11→- 150g tomatoes, diced\n    12→- 1 onion, sliced\n    13→- 4 garlic cloves, minced\n    14→- 1 red pepper, diced\n    15→- 150ml olive oil\n    16→- 1 generous pinch saffron threads\n    17→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    18→- Fresh parsley for garnish\n    19→- Lemon wedges for serving\n    20→\n    21→Method:\n    22→1. Heat broth and steep saffron threads in it\n    23→2. Heat oil in a large paella pan\n    24→3. Sauté onion, garlic, and pepper until soft\n    25→4. Add rice and stir to coat with oil\n    26→5. Pour in the hot broth gradually\n    27→6. Do not stir - let the rice cook undisturbed\n    28→7. Add beans and tomatoes after 15 minutes\n    29→8. Continue cooking until rice is tender and liquid absorbed (20-25 min total)\n    30→9. When a light golden crust forms on bottom, it's ready\n    31→10. Remove from heat, cover with foil, rest 5 minutes\n    32→11. Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges\n    33→\n    34→Cooking time: 30 minutes\n    35→Serves: 6 people\n    36→Difficulty: Medium\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"514ae0ce-35bb-47a4-9ae9-1445f9f3d1eb","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Paella Valenciana.generated.18.txt","content":"PAELLA\nVALENCIANA\n\nTraditional Spanish rice dish from Valencia region\n\nIngredients:\n- 400g short-grain rice (bomba or arborio)\n- 1 liter chicken or vegetable broth\n- 150g green beans\n- 100g butter beans\n- 150g tomatoes, diced\n- 1 onion, sliced\n- 4 garlic cloves, minced\n- 1 red pepper, diced\n- 150ml olive oil\n- 1 generous pinch saffron threads\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh parsley for garnish\n- Lemon wedges for serving\n\nMethod:\n1. Heat broth and steep saffron threads in it\n2. Heat oil in a large paella pan\n3. Sauté onion, garlic, and pepper until soft\n4. Add rice and stir to coat with oil\n5. Pour in the hot broth gradually\n6. Do not stir - let the rice cook undisturbed\n7. Add beans and tomatoes after 15 minutes\n8. Continue cooking until rice is tender and liquid absorbed (20-25 min total)\n9. When a light golden crust forms on bottom, it's ready\n10. Remove from heat, cover with foil, rest 5 minutes\n11. Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges\n\nCooking time: 30 minutes\nServes: 6 people\nDifficulty: Medium","numLines":36,"startLine":1,"totalLines":36}}}
