{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W1Cwyo8K98HjChpaiRDQtR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The feedback file has been written to `tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/feedback.md`.\n\nHere's a summary of what I found:\n\n## 8 Root-Cause Patterns\n\n**Pattern 1 (largest ~20 failures): ALL_CAPS vs. Title Case mismatch**\nThe algorithm returns verbatim OCR casing. Files like `BARSZCZ`, `BEEF STEW`, `PLACKI SEROWE` are returned in ALL_CAPS but expected as `Barszcz`, `Beef Stew`, `Placki Serowe`. No case normalization exists.\n\n**Pattern 2: Polish `ze` preposition triggers garbled filter**\n`Krem Grzybowy ze Śmietaną` and `Konfitury ze Liwek` both fail because `ze` (2-letter Polish preposition) is not in `commonShort2`. The entire title line is discarded as \"garbled\" and the algorithm picks something else.\n\n**Pattern 3: Two-word split title destroyed by dedup**\n`Lamb` + `Stew` (on separate lines) both become valid single-line candidates. The 2-line join `Lamb Stew` is then removed by dedup (\"shorter wins\") since it contains `Lamb` and `Stew` as substrings. Returns `Lamb + Stew`.\n\n**Pattern 4: `Zupy` in SECTION_LABELS blocks 3-line title**\n`Zupy Zimowe Warzywne` split across 3 lines — but `Zupy` is a section label so 2-line and 3-line joins starting from it are never generated.\n\n**Pattern 5: Long OCR garbage prologue bypasses burst detection**\n~35 lines of repeated cooking instruction fragments (> 20 chars each) skip `findBurstEnd`. Lines like `Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, then fold` pass hard filters and crowd out the real title which sits at 70%+ through the document.\n\n**Pattern 6: `SEZON: WIOSNA` header beats mixed-case title**\nSeason headers before the actual title get structural heading bonus + position bonus and win over the real title (e.g., `Beet Salad`, `Coleslaw`).\n\n**Pattern 7: `(` continuation merges English subtitle glosses**\n`PIEROGI RUSKIE\\n(Boiled Dumplings...)` → merged into `PIEROGI RUSKIE (Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)`. Designed for `(VARIATION D)` patterns, it over-fires on translator glosses.\n\n**Pattern 8: Compound title removed by dedup**\n`HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION` (line 1) contains `DILL SAUCE VARIATION` (line 32) as a substring, so dedup removes the compound title in favor of the shorter substring."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4431,"cache_read_input_tokens":95917,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4431},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0bd2458-e6bc-4fcb-9e45-2dd61b6b2106","uuid":"e2af2ffa-0502-40ef-880e-97276fb6037b"}
